h, on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Big_12s_First_Session-45.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Big_12s_First_Session-45.jpg"><media:title>emerson smith</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Big_12s_First_Session-45.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 18:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58906</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Complete Sweep of BYU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/baseball-mountaineers-complete-sweep-of-byu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/baseball-mountaineers-complete-sweep-of-byu</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/21/DSC00667.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 20 West Virginia University baseball team defeated BYU, 11-1, in eight innings, Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark to complete the three-game sweep. The Mountaineers improve to 16-4 and 5-1 in the Big 12 while the Cougars fall to 10-12 and 2-4 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/DSC00667.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/DSC00667.jpg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/DSC00667.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 17:34:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58905</s:story_id></item><item><title>Golf Heads to The Hootie at Bulls Bay</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/golf-heads-to-the-hootie-at-bulls-bay</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/golf-heads-to-the-hootie-at-bulls-bay</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Hootie" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/21/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Hootie.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University golf team will return to action on Sunday at The Hootie at Bulls Bay Intercollegiate in Awendaw, South Carolina.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Hootie.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Hootie.jpg"><media:title>Hootie</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/GOLF26_Matchup_1920x1080_Hootie.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 11:32:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58903</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Come Up Short in Tight Match Against No. 35 Arizona</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/tennis-mountaineers-come-up-short-in-tight-match-against-no-35-arizona</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/tennis-mountaineers-come-up-short-in-tight-match-against-no-35-arizona</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Lyla Byers" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/21/ex1-10__1_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (6-9, 0-8 Big 12) dropped a tightly contested 4-1 decision to No. 35 Arizona (13-8, 4-3 Big 12) on Saturday morning at the Summit Tennis Academy.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/ex1-10__1_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/ex1-10__1_.jpg"><media:title>Lyla Byers</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/ex1-10__1_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 15:17:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58904</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>